# Astro Rules

## File Role

- Keep `src/pages/` thin. Prefer importing a page-level module or composition rather than building large pages inline.
- Use `.astro` for page shells, layout composition, static sections, and server-side data preparation.
- Use `.tsx` islands for interactive UI, browser-only state, event handlers, and subscriptions.

## Frontmatter

- Keep frontmatter focused on imports, props, and straightforward data shaping.
- Prefer loading or preparing data in frontmatter and passing it down through props.
- Avoid duplicating client-side logic in Astro when the interactive component already owns that behavior.

## Structure

- Shared page wrappers belong in `src/modules/` or `src/components/`, not directly in `src/pages/`.
- Reuse the existing `Layout` pattern for document-level concerns such as global styles, metadata, and shared head/body structure.
- Prefer path aliases from `tsconfig.json` for imports.

## Styling

- Prefer Tailwind utility classes for page composition and simple sections.
- When a section needs bespoke styling, colocate that styling with the component or module instead of expanding global CSS unnecessarily.
